"use strict";(self.webpackChunkta_web=self.webpackChunkta_web||[]).push([[8],{397:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"2notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/notions/2notions","source":"@site/notions/2022-05-08-Second-Pnotions.md","title":"2 Pnotions","description":"Hello everyone,","date":"2022-05-08T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 8, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":2.08,"truncated":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"2notions","title":"2 Pnotions"},"nextItem":{"title":"1 Pnotions","permalink":"/notions/Fnotions"}},"content":"Hello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Bored Ape Yacht Club creator\u2019s metaverse mint rocks the Ethereum blockchain](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/1/23051974/bored-ape-yacht-club-metaverse-mint-rocked-ethereum-blockchain-otherside-otherdeeds-yuga-labs)\\n\\nYuga Labs, the web3 company behind the Bored Ape Yacht Club, disrupted the entire Ethereum blockchain as a flood of users rushed to purchase NFTs representing virtual plots of land in its upcoming metaverse project, Otherside.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Apple Mail Now Blocks Email Tracking. Here\u2019s What It Means for You](https://www.wired.com/story/apple-mail-blocks-email-tracking-heres-what-it-means/)\\n\\nIf you don\u2019t like marketers (or anyone else) knowing when and where you read your email, Apple\u2019s feature will help you reclaim some privacy.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Heroku resets user passwords after concluding April cyber-attack ran deep](https://portswigger.net/daily-swig/heroku-resets-user-passwords-after-concluding-april-cyber-attack-ran-deep)\\n\\nHeroku, the Salesforce-owned cloud application platform, began the forced reset of user passwords on May 4.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Twitter\u2019s decentralized, open-source offshoot just released its first code](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/4/23057473/twitter-bluesky-adx-release-open-source-decentralized-social-network)\\n\\nBluesky, Twitter\u2019s open-source offshoot, has released early code for a decentralized social network protocol.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [What Is Web3? The Confusing Term, Explained](https://www.cnet.com/personal-finance/crypto/what-is-web3-the-confusing-term-explained/)\\n\\nThe more complicated but more specific way to think about Web3 is an internet owned by users.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [An unlikely database migration](https://tailscale.com/blog/an-unlikely-database-migration/)\\n\\n\u201cSo, what database do you use?\u201d\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Dockerfiles now Support Multiple Build Contexts](https://www.docker.com/blog/dockerfiles-now-support-multiple-build-contexts/?fbclid=IwAR2jXY0DQMtL5Bux0nCQ9V_Toas8dUJolIpJby6JMzbPazh3u0Ks6XpyLAc)\\n\\nThis means you can use files from different local directories as part of your build.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The differences between Docker, containerd, CRI-O and runc](https://www.tutorialworks.com/difference-docker-containerd-runc-crio-oci/)\\n\\n The main standards around containers that you should be aware of.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Virtual Kubernetes clusters: A new model for multitenancy](https://opensource.com/article/22/3/virtual-kubernetes-clusters-new-model-multitenancy)\\n\\nA virtual cluster is a shared Kubernetes cluster that appears to the tenant as a dedicated cluster.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Pulumi YAML: A Simple Declarative Interface for Pulumi](https://www.pulumi.com/blog/pulumi-yaml/?utm_source=LinkedIn&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=blog&hsa_acc=508076010&hsa_cam=621179916&hsa_grp=182712696&hsa_ad=184998386&hsa_net=linkedin&hsa_ver=3&li_fat_id=268a2c26-5017-4d7a-992f-f9af779c9435)\\n\\nIt is a simple YAML-based interface to the entirety of the Pulumi Infrastructure as Code platform.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Compromising Read-Only Containers with Fileless Malware](https://sysdig.com/blog/containers-read-only-fileless-malware/)\\n\\nBy making the file system unable to be altered, it prevents an attacker from writing their malware executable to disk.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Warren Buffett gives his most expansive explanation for why he doesn\u2019t believe in bitcoin](https://www.cnbc.com/2022/04/30/warren-buffett-gives-his-most-expansive-explanation-for-why-he-doesnt-believe-in-bitcoin.html)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Top 5 Worst Programming Languages](https://catonmat.net/5-worst-programming-languages)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [IBM\'s asshole test](https://johnpublic.mataroa.blog/blog/the-asshole-test/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Google Docs crashed when fed \'And. And. And. And. And.\'](https://www.theregister.com/2022/05/06/google_docs_crash/)\\n\\n## Crazy star of the week\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Totally fungible Ape](https://www.ykilcher.com/apes)\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\nThis week\u2019s comic - Dilbert (main character, an engineer), Pointy-haired boss (The oblivious manager)\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/Pnotions2.jpg)\\n\\nUntil next time,\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nMy newsletter [#2 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/2-pnotions?s=w) <br></br>\\n*Checkout my Ape FT in the comments*"},{"id":"Fnotions","metadata":{"permalink":"/notions/Fnotions","source":"@site/notions/2022-05-01-First-Pnotions.md","title":"1 Pnotions","description":"Hello everyone,","date":"2022-05-01T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 1, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":2.36,"truncated":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"Fnotions","title":"1 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"2 Pnotions","permalink":"/notions/2notions"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome","permalink":"/notions/notions"}},"content":"Hello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Cloudflare blocks 15M rps HTTPS DDoS attack](https://blog.cloudflare.com/15m-rps-ddos-attack/)\\n\\nEarlier this month, Cloudflare\u2019s systems automatically detected and mitigated a 15.3 million request-per-second (rps) DDoS attack \u2014 one of the largest HTTPS DDoS attacks on record.\\n\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Log4j Attack Surface Remains Massive](https://www.darkreading.com/threat-intelligence/l0g4j-attack-surface-remains-huge)\\n\\nFour months after the Log4Shell vulnerability was disclosed, most affected open source components remain unpatched, and companies continue to use vulnerable versions of the logging tool.\\n\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [India reveals plan to become major RISC-V design and production player by 2023](https://www.theregister.com/2022/04/29/india_risc_v_microprocessor_program/)\\n\\nIndia\'s government has announced a plan and roadmap for local semiconductor design and production, based on the open source RISC-V architecture, and set a goal of delivering world-class silicon by the end of next year.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Telegram now lets users send cryptocurrency through TON blockchain spinoff](https://www.theverge.com/2022/4/30/23050263/telegram-lets-users-send-cryptocurrency-chats-toncoin-ton)\\n\\nTelegram now lets users send Toncoin, the cryptocurrency built off of Telegram\u2019s abandoned blockchain effort, directly from chats within the messaging app.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e And, yeah, Elon Musk bought Twitter.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Progressive Delivery with Argo Rollouts : Blue-Green Deployment ](https://www.infracloud.io/blogs/progressive-delivery-argo-rollouts-blue-green-deployment/)\\n\\nProgressive delivery was introduced which enables the delivery of software with the right changes to the right amount of customers at the right time.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Kubectl detector for docker socket](https://github.com/aws-containers/kubectl-detector-for-docker-socket)\\n\\nA Kubectl plugin that can detect if any of your workloads or manifest files are mounting the docker.sock volume.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Spotify Live: From Live to Recording ](https://engineering.atspotify.com/2022/04/spotify-live-from-live-to-recording/)\\n\\nSpotify Live (formerly Spotify Greenroom) is a platform that democratizes live audio streams. Creators are able to create rooms and stream live directly to fans who join the room.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Automatically Detect Operational Issues in Lambda Functions with Amazon DevOps Guru for Serverless](https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/automatically-detect-operational-issues-in-lambda-functions-with-amazon-devops-guru-for-serverless/)\\n\\nIt allows developers to improve the operational performance and availability of serverless applications.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [AWS CIDR finder](https://github.com/cooperwalbrun/aws-cidr-finder/blob/master/README.md) - To quickly find unused CIDR blocks in your AWS VPC\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Kubernetes 1.25 Release Team Shadow Application](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSe7N7wFTpLhjBogs4UZJAnyZ9BVRNtBp3GzV8LZRY2op2sIAw/viewform)\\n\\nIf you are interested in contributing to Kubernetes, start the journey here.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Be careful with that thing, it\u2019s a confidential coffee maker](https://devblogs.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20220426-00/?p=106528) - My favorite article of the week.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Is crypto just one big Ponzi scheme?](https://unherd.com/thepost/is-crypto-just-one-big-ponzi-scheme/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Please Don\'t Say Just Hello In Chat](https://nohello.net/en/) - Please don\u2019t.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [My crazy DNS dream](https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/my-crazy-dns-dream-prashanthi-sadde/?trackingId=DzsV0lNCTlCyiXDFwXB2UQ%3D%3D) - I was working late on a DNS issue when I wrote this article. I wanted to share a fun version of my pain. I wrote this around 2:30 AM, published it, and went to sleep.\\n\\nIf you are wondering, yes, I solved the issue.\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\nI love comics. Here is one of my favorites. It\u2019s a conversation between the Brain and Heart.\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/phb_w.jpg)\\n\\nUntil next time,\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nMy newsletter [#1 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/1-pnotions?r=1gxugq&s=w&utm_campaign=post&utm_medium=web)"},{"id":"notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/notions/notions","source":"@site/notions/index.md","title":"Welcome","description":"Beginning of the initial stage","date":"2021-04-27T23:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 27, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.84,"truncated":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"notions","title":"Welcome","date":"2021-04-27T23:00"},"prevItem":{"title":"1 Pnotions","permalink":"/notions/Fnotions"}},"content":"### Beginning of the initial stage\\n\\nTL;DR <br></br>\\nI am starting `Pnotions`, a blog, and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on Technology and Engineering. I will meet you every Sunday, 7 AM IST (starting May1, 2022). If you like my letters, go crazy [Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/) \ud83d\udc7d\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nI have given a lot of thought to this section. What to do, what to share, etc. Then I realized that I was overthinking this. Yeah, I do that a lot. So, it is time to do something.\\n\\nIn the initial stage of Pnotions, I would like to share some of the articles from my reading list with everyone. I will share the posts here every Sunday morning, and you can also subscribe to my weekly newsletter.\\n\\nThis is my new tag `#Pnotions`. Every article I share from now on will have this tag.\\n\\n### And, my weekly newsletter, every Sunday morning \ud83c\udf89\\n\\n## Subscribe here [Pnotions Newsletter](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/coming-soon?r=1gxugq&s=w&utm_campaign=post&utm_medium=web)\\n*The first newsletter, starting this Sunday (May 1, 2022)*\\n\\n![hi](../static/img/pnotions.svg)"}]}')}}]);